  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It seems that since Geth updated to 1.10.1, Truffle's CI has been consistently failing. The main change that occurred in that release was that the Berlin hard-fork was enabled. See [the release notes](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/releases/tag/v1.10.1). When Geth was pinned to 1.9.25 CI seemed to run successfully (see https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/pull/3911).\r\n\r\n~Since the Berlin hard-fork is scheduled for mid-April, we need to investigate what Truffle needs to do to be compliant.~\r\n\r\n**Update**: It turns out that the real incompatibility has to do with a functionality that Geth enabled in v1.10.0. As of that version they disallow transactions that are not compliant with EIP-115. This causes Truffle's transactions to fail.",
